      "note_no": "1551",
      "note": "Grasp of the forelock: an Arabic idiom, referring to a horse's forelock. The man who grasps it has complete power over the horse, and for the horse the forelock is as it were the crown of his beauty, the sum of his power of selfassertion. So Allah's power over all creatures is unlimited and no one can withstand His decree. Cf. 96:15-16."
