      "note_no": "80",
      "note": "I.e., there is no living being over which He has not complete control and which is not entirely dependent on Him (cf. verse 6 of this surah). When describing a person's humility and subjection to another person, the ancient Arabs used to say, \"The forelock of so-and-so is in the hand of so-and-so\". See in this connection 96:15-16, where this idiomatic expression occurs for the first time in the chronological order of Qur'anic revelation."
